From 3ffdd54ed041f879a9687915d4c0e0397285d05a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 14:54:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Remove stray patch/reject files and actually fix location
 keyword bug

- Removed leftover .patch files and .rej reject files that got
  committed by mistake during earlier patch troubleshooting. These
  were never meant to be part of the repo history, and the .rej
  files meant the real LiveChat.tsx / Navbar.tsx source was never
  actually updated despite the commit message saying so.
- LiveChat: actually applied the fix this time -- the pet FAQ's
  'cat' keyword was matching as a substring inside 'location'
  (lo-cat-ion) because keyword matching used plain string.includes().
  Typing 'Location?' was answered with the pets policy instead of
  the resort's address. Switched matching to word-boundary regex
  (\bkeyword\b) so short keywords only match whole words.
